text: Why are we taught to discard our thoughts of suicide We re essentially taught that having suicidal thoughts is a bad thing  If we mention our suicidal thoughts to others  we re told to go see a counselor  take medication  or call the suicide hotline  all of which will try to steer us away from such thoughts  Or  we re advised to make some changes to our daily life to make ourselves  feel better  exercise  eat better  sleep more  join a club  etc  Despite doing these things  if the suicidal thoughts are still there  doesn t that mean something  Why are people trying to have us essentially discard such thoughts Speaking for myself now  maybe despite all the positive changes we re making  we just can t find a place for ourselves in the world  Maybe we are just tired of mental suffering  Maybe we feel fundamentally incompatible with society  I understand that committing suicide negatively impacts others  but maybe  at the very least  society should be taught to stop fearing suicidal ideation  Then at least we don t have to go through this alone
summary: People are taught to discard their suicidal thoughts. Maybe people can't find a place for themselves in the world. Maybe they are tired of mental suffering or they feel fundamentally incompatible with society. Maybe society should be taught to stop fearing suicidal ideation.
